Title: Determinantes de la deserción y graduación universitaria: Una
aplicación utilizando modelos de duración.
Abstract: This study examines the issue of student departure from a public university. Non-parametric
proportional hazard models are used to estimate the quantity and quality effects of the students’
personal and socioeconomic characteristics on the probability of their dropping out or graduating. Data
include a cohort of students who started studying accounting at National University of Rosario,
Argentina, in 1991. The results are useful to evaluate and design public policies in the educational
sector.
